This arrangement in two categories of increased airway resistance and decreased lung compliance follows the general law of motion of the respiratory system [10], where the pressure applied to the lung (P
APPL) generates a flow of gas (V) that is opposed by the airways’ resistance (R
AW) and that results in a change in lung volume (V
T) that is facilitated by the respiratory compliance (C):24.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
