\end{document}PAPPL=PMUS+PVENT=V·×RAW+VT×1/C,where P
APPL equals the sum of the pressure generated by the respiratory muscles (P
MUS), a negative pressure, and the pressure generated by the ventilator (P
VENT), a positive pressure. Thinking in these terms greatly assists the understanding of the mechanical phenomena of respiratory disorders and their interaction with mechanical ventilation.

