$$ C=\varDelta V/P, $$
\end{document}C=ΔV/P,where ∆V is the difference in lung volume between end inspiration and end expiration, i.e., the V
T; P is the end-inspiratory pressure at 0 inspiratory flow, i.e., the P
PLAT. Hence:24.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
